“The first clip features a humpback whale rising from the middle of a baitball in absolutely perfect conditions! This whale's name is Snowflake. Snowflake is a very special whale to me as it is the first humpback whale I ever saw breach and the first whale that ever ‘mugged’ me…

“In the whale watching world, ‘mugging’ refers to the moment a whale sticks its head out of the water, making eye contact. Snowflake seemed to recognize our voices. It was a beautiful and life-changing moment.”

“The first clip features a humpback whale rising from the middle of a baitball in absolutely perfect conditions! This whale's name is Snowflake. Snowflake is a very special whale to me as it is the first humpback whale I ever saw breach and the first whale that ever ‘mugged’ me…

“In the whale watching world, ‘mugging’ refers to the moment a whale sticks its head out of the water, making eye contact. Snowflake seemed to recognize our voices. It was a beautiful and life-changing moment.”

Naude Dreyer (@namib_naude) and his friend Antonie rescued this huge seal on February 26. This seal was so strong he dragged them both around and he didn’t actually fit into the net, that’s why they struggled so long to get him down! He had a very deeply embedded packing strap that must have caused immense pain. It's really amazing to see him getting rescued. Thanks to @oceanconservationnamibia .

node.text:
Meet the SHIFF ARMS JELLYFISH! (Or barrel jellyfish)
Otherwise known by its scientific name, the 'Rhizostoma Pulmo', this Jellyfish is the largest in all of British-territorial waters! Don't let the beautiful blue color fool you though, these Jellys' stings are incredibly painful so DO NOT TOUCH!
They are quite beautiful to observe from afar!
Photo by © @davidantoja 
Video by © @ayvalik3sea
